# React + TypeScript conventions

- Prefer small pure functions (`normalizeText`, `makeId`) over inline logic, but don’t over-abstract.
- Prefer `useMemo` only when it improves clarity or avoids repeated work; don’t memoize everything.
- Use stable ids/keys and avoid array index keys.
- Keep state updates immutable; use functional `setState(prev => ...)` when derived from previous state.
- Keep event handlers typed via inference; avoid `any`.
- For form submit flows: prevent default, validate input, then update state; keep submit buttons disabled when invalid.
- Favor readable JSX: avoid deeply nested ternaries; extract a small component if it gets hard to scan.

